cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with graph classification using convolutional neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Given that the paper proposes a novel way to represent graphs as multi-channel image-like structures that can be handled by 2D CNNs, it is highly likely to be classified under cs.LG and cs.CV. The use of neural networks and artificial intelligence techniques also makes cs.NE and cs.AI likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with social and information networks, which makes cs.SI a possible sub-category as well.
